## Best Practices

1. Always use TypeScript types for props, emits, and function parameters
2. Use Vue 3 Composition API with `<script setup>` syntax
3. Follow the kebab-case for event names (`@update-name` not `@updateName`)
4. Use PascalCase for component names
5. Structure imports with external libraries first, then local imports
6. Use proper error handling with try/catch for async operations
7. Use the @/ alias for imports from the src directory
8. Follow the Tailwind CSS utility-first approach for styling
9. For API calls, use auto-generated hooks from the API client (see @.cursor/rules/frontend/api_call.mdc)
10. Keep components focused and single-purpose
